Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop a deep #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium heat a drizzle of @oil{}. Melt in the @Butter{20%grams}.

Once melted, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} until coated, ~{1%minute}. Add @salt{1/4%tsp} and the @Water for the Rice{300%milliliter} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Pan-fry the @THIS™ Isn't Chicken Plant-Based Pieces{170%grams} until golden brown, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add half the @Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet} and toss to coat, ~{1%minute}.

Once cooked, transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the onion and fry until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir in the @Korma Curry Paste{50%grams} and remaining curry powder. Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Curry{150%milliliter}. Bring to the boil and simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams}, @Peas{120%grams} and the cooked THIS™ Isn't Chicken korma curry. Stir to combine, bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @?water{} if it's a little thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your serving bowls.

Top with the THIS™ Isn't Chicken korma curry. Enjoy!